LAGOS – The operatives of the La­gos State Environmental and Special Offences En­forcement Unit, otherwise known as Task Force, have impounded 100 commercial motorcycles in Lagos for allegedly plying unautho­rised routes in the state. It said the exercise was in continuation of govern­ment efforts to bring sanity on Lagos roads and get rid of defiant motorcyclists on restricted routes. Adebayo Taofiq, Head, Public Affairs Unit, La­gos State Task Force, in a statement made available to Daily Independent, said the operation that led to the seizures was carried out over the weekend. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Chairman of the Agency, CSP Shola Jejeloye ,who led the enforcement exercise, also disclosed that the 100 commercial mo­torcycles were impound­ed around Navy Town at Alakija, 2nd Rainbow and Festac Town. He asserted that the enforcement operation was carried out to halt the abuse of traffic laws by mo­torcycle operators. 20 Burnt Beyond Recognition In Bauchi Auto-crash Osun Senator Attacked By Armed Thugs CSP Jejeloye added that apart from criminals using motorcycles as a means to escape after criminal activities, the influx into the state of these illegal motorcyclists without any traceable address and valid means of identification re­mains a huge Security and Safety threat to residents.